Nobody had any demand upon Servilius, and no charge to make against him (quum ageret nemo, nemo postularet). Verres compelled him to make a ‘sponsio' with his own ‘ lictor,' the effect of which was to try the question whether Servilius was a thief or not; rather a singular way of dealing with a man’s character, when there was no charge against him.
